I think a single conditional would make this a bit easier to parse. Maybe with something like this?
String funcName;
int defaultPrecision;
switch (type) {
    case CurrentTime.Type.TIMESTAMP:
        funcName = ...
        break;

    case CurrentTime.Type.TIME:
        funcName = ...
        break;


    default:
      return visitExpression(node, context);
}
return allocateFunction(...
I think it would also be an option to make the default precision argument optional and keep the "what value is the default" knowledge encapsulated within the function itself. So that the expression analyzer doesn't add the argument if it is not specified.

