nodes.bodyText:
I think it would be cool if we could de-couple more of the time related logic into more specific components. The TransactionContext should only be concerned about caching the value retrieved to ensure the same value is re-used across the transaction. It shouldn't know too much about how that value is produced.
For example we could introduce a Clocks class that encapsulates the logic about fixing/mocking the current time.
Maybe even work with the Clock classes directly instead of the Supplier<Long>.
There is both
Clock.systemUTC();
Clock.fixed(..);

